94
00:08:29,319 --> 00:08:30,000
Give us your judgment.

95
00:08:30,720 --> 00:08:32,399
Since ancient times, building tombs

96
00:08:32,399 --> 00:08:33,600
involves mounds and trees.

97
00:08:33,679 --> 00:08:35,159
Trees are the markers of tombs,

98
00:08:35,159 --> 00:08:36,600
planted in front of the burial mounds

99
00:08:36,600 --> 00:08:38,120
to make the tomb's layout

100
00:08:38,120 --> 00:08:39,799
capable of blessing the descendants.

101
00:08:39,960 --> 00:08:41,000
Since the Shang and Zhou dynasties,

102
00:08:41,000 --> 00:08:42,559
China has had the theory of Feng Shui.

103
00:08:42,559 --> 00:08:43,759
Burying the dead

104
00:08:43,759 --> 00:08:44,759
has always emphasized

105
00:08:44,759 --> 00:08:46,799
embracing yin and yang, relying on mountains and water.

106
00:08:47,519 --> 00:08:49,600
But putting a coffin inside a tree,

107
00:08:50,000 --> 00:08:51,120
I've never heard of that.

108
00:08:51,120 --> 00:08:52,480
It's highly improper.

109
00:08:53,159 --> 00:08:56,159
Judging from the reliefs on the coffin,

110
00:08:56,759 --> 00:08:58,559
although slightly rigid,

111
